snippet: The dispute follows Australia’s admission that its naval vessels inadvertently entered Indonesian waters while seeking to intercept boat people.
abstract: Indonesian government says the country will increase maritime security patrols following an admission by Australia of breaching Indonesia's territorial waters; announcement is the latest diplomatic row between the two countries over asylum seekers.
lead_paragraph: The dispute follows Australia’s admission that its naval vessels inadvertently entered Indonesian waters while seeking to intercept boat people.

headline.main: Tension Rises Between Australia and Indonesia Over Migrant Patrols
headline.print_headline: Indonesia: Australia to Offer an Apology
